messages.message:
*Summary for Cypress On-Call for August 19-23*
It was a calm week for Cypress last week! I also did not have to do a lot as on-call because other engineers like @Jessica, @Serena, and @Xindi Xu proactively did tasks like reminding people to fix/unskip tests, raise up flaky tests and debug! So thank you from everyone for that :raised_hands:

• `workspaces-drives-crud` and `drives` will continue to be non-blocking and failing due to a backend bug
• Other tests that were failing on sandbox have now been fixed or skipped
• There were many flaky tests on friday due to the crafting-cyp sandbox being very slow. After some debugging, @sean.donohoe found that it was due to the sandbox's cluster size not being set correctly. After he corrected that, the flaky tests started to pass.
In general, if you have skipped a test in the past or recently, lets look into those again and check if they can be unskipped!
